The paper discusses the integration of online and offline channels to bridge the virtual and physical worlds, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (HCI) and falls under the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of extended reality (XR) and mixed reality (MR), which are related to computer graphics and multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of teleoperated robots and edge computing, which are related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
